ag|Spain}}\n|Assassination of [[Antonio C\u00e1novas del Castillo]], [[Prime Minister of Spain]]. \n|Anarchists led by the Italian [[Michele Angiolillo]] \n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==1900\u20131929==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Type\n!data-sort-type=\"number\" | Dead\n!data-sort-type=\"number\" | Injured\n!Location\n!class=\"unsortable\"|Details\n!Perpetrator\n!Part of<br />\n|-\n|29 July 1900\n|Assassination\n|1\n|0\n||{{flagicon|Italy}} [[Monza]], [[Italy]]\n|Gaetano Bresci, an Italian-American Anarchist, assassinated [[Umberto I of Italy]]\n|[[Gaetano Bresci]]\n|\n|-\n|15 April 1902\n|Assassination\n|1\n|0\n||{{flagicon|Russian Empire}} [[St.Petersburg]], [[Russia]]\n|Minister of the Interior [[Dmitry Sipyagin]] was assassinated in the Marinsky Theatre. \n|[[Stepan Balmashov]]\n|\n|-\n|28 April \u2013 1 May 1903\n|Bombings\n|0 (+4)\n|\n|{{flagicon|Ottoman Empire}} [[Thessaloniki]], [[Ottoman Empire]]\n|Members of the [[Boatmen of Thessalon\u00edki]], a [[Bulgarians|Bulgarian]] [[anarchism|anarchist]] group, carried out a series of bombings in [[Thessaloniki]]\n|[[Boatmen of Thessalon\u00edki]]\n|\n|-\n|18 May 1904\n|Kidnapping\n|0\n|2 kidnapped\n||{{flagicon|Morocco}} [[Morocco]] \n|[[Ion Perdicaris]] and Cromwell Varley were [[kidnapping|kidnapped]] and held for ransom by [[bandit]] [[Mulai Ahmed er Raisuli]] in Morocco.<ref>{{cite news|title=PERDICARIS AND VARLEY ARE IN GRAVE DANGER; An American Resident of Tangier Tells of the Situation |date=22 May 1904 |work=The New York Times |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9F07E5D91E3BE631A25751C2A9639C946597D6CF |accessdate=2015-03-05}}</ref>\n|[[Mulai Ahmed er Raisuli]]\n|\n|-\n|15 February 1905\n|Bombing\n|2\n|1+\n||{{flagicon|Russian Empire}}  [[Russia]]\n|Assassination of [[Grand Duke Sergei Alexandrovich of Russia|Grand Duke Serge Alexandrovich Romanov]] by Socialist-revolutionaries. His coach driver Andrei Rudinkin was also killed.\n|[[Ivan Kalyayev]]\n|\n|-\n|31 May 1906\n|Bombing\n|24\n|